About Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University

Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University is the leading and one of the oldest{" "} MCI approved medical colleges in Ukraine {" "} that consists of total of 12 hospitals and clinics. More than 4000 students from all over the world study medicine at this University. It is one of the best places for students who want to study medicine in Ukraine{" "} at affordable fees. The degree awarded to the students at the end of the MBBS course is a Medical doctor (MD) degree.

Indian Student Admission Procedure

Indian students need to follow the below steps to{" "} study medicine in Ukraine:

  • {" "} The students need to apply online at the university website & fill all the details and can send the documents through email.
  • {" "} When the documents will be evaluated, the students will be notified regarding acceptance or rejection of the application.
  • {" "} The eligible students will receive an admission confirmation letter within 2-3 working days.
  • {" "} Then the students need to make the payment of their admission.
  • {" "} The students will also receive admission letter along with the invitation letter.
  • {" "} The students can then apply for the visa.

Eligibility Criteria of Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University

The eligibility criteria of the students who want to{" "} study medicine in Ukraine are as follows:

  • {" "} The students should have science in their 12th standard and should have an aggregate of 50% marks in physics, chemistry, and Biology.
  • {" "} The students should be at least 17 years of age to take admission in MCI approved medical colleges in Ukraine.
  • {" "} The students should also qualify for the NEET exam with passing marks to study medicine in Ukraine.
  • {" "} The students should have English subject in their higher secondary.
  • {" "} The students must not be more than 25 years of age.
Requirements for MBBS Admission

The necessary documents for taking admission in{" "} MCI approved medical colleges in Ukraine are the following:

  • {" "} A complete filled application form with all accurate details.
  • {" "} Original and photocopies of Passport.
  • {" "} Birth certificates and other mandatory certificates must be submitted to the concerned authority.
  • {" "} Passport size (3cmX4cm) photographs.
  • {" "} Original and a photocopy of mark sheets of both 10th & 12th standard
  • {" "} A scorecard of NEFT (if required)
  • {" "} Transfer certificate from the previous school
  • {" "} Leaving certificate from the concerned school
  • {" "} A certificate of code of conduct must be submitted
  • {" "} The bank copy of guardians must be submitted which indicates that they have sufficient funds to pay the fees.
  • {" "} A medical checkup certificate is also essential

Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University provides the following facilities:

  • {" "} It has computer labs and laboratories with modern equipment
Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University Advantages for Indian Student

Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University provides the following advantages to the Indian students:

  • {" "} The medium of teaching is English in this university.
  • {" "} The fee structure of MBBS course in Ivano Frankivsk National Medical University is very affordable.

  • {" "} It is one of the best destinations to conduct medical research work.
